Get German referendum proposal name's grammatical gender

Source: R/fokus.gen.R
proposal_name_gender.Rd

Returns the grammatical gender of the German name of the specified referendum proposal.

Usage

proposal_name_gender(
  ballot_date = pal::pkg_config_val("ballot_date"),
  lvl = lvls(ballot_date, canton, ballot_type = "referendum"),
  canton = cantons(ballot_date),
  proposal_nr = 1L,
  type = all_name_types
)

Arguments

ballot_date

FOKUS-covered ballot date. One of

  • "2018-09-23"

  • "2018-11-25"

  • "2019-10-20"

  • "2020-09-27"

  • "2020-10-18"

  • "2021-11-28"

  • "2023-06-18"

  • "2024-10-20"

lvl

Political level. One of "cantonal" or "federal".

canton

FOKUS-covered canton name. One of

  • "aargau"

Only relevant if lvl = "cantonal".

proposal_nr

Proposal number. A positive integerish scalar.

type

Name type. One of "short" or "long".

Value

A character scalar.

See also

Other proposal predicate functions: argument_proposal_nrs(), combos_proposal_arguments(), combos_proposal_main_motives(), combos_proposals(), has_proposal_arguments(), has_proposal_main_motives(), is_proposal_name_plural(), main_motive_proposal_nrs(), n_proposal_arguments(), n_proposal_main_motives(), proposal_argument(), proposal_arguments(), proposal_main_motives(), proposal_name(), proposal_type()

Examples

fokus::proposal_name_gender(ballot_date = "2018-09-23",
                            lvl = "federal",
                            proposal_nr = 1,
                            type = "short")
#> [1] "feminine"
                            
fokus::proposal_name_gender(ballot_date = "2018-09-23",
                            lvl = "federal",
                            proposal_nr = 1,
                            type = "long")
#> [1] "masculine"
